place.name: TILNEY CUM ISLINGTON
place.gazetteerText: TILNEY-CUM-ISLINGTON, a parish, with a village, in the district of Wisbeach and county of Norfolk; 2½ miles SW by S of Clenchwarton r. station, and 4 SW of Lynn. Post town, Lynn. Acres, 1,625. Real property, £3,598. Pop., 295. Houses, 61. The manor belongs to R. Bagge, Esq. Islington Hall is the seat of Mrs. Hulton. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £110.* Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
